  
                    
                        
                
                Steven Fletcher (centre) and Ryan Fraser (second right) scored in the first half for ScotlandScotland thumped 10-man Albania to go level on points with Israel at the top of Nations League Group C1. Ryan Fraser and James Forrest scored their first goals for Scotland, while a Steven Fletcher penalty was his first goal for his country in over two years.Albania's chances were not helped by Mergim Mavraj's red card after he headbutted Ryan Christie at 1-0.
    
        
A win over Israel on Tuesday at Hampden will see Scotland win the group and seize a play-off spot.And, with that, they would be just two games away from Euro 2020 qualification should they not have already earned it through the qualifying groups which begin next year.The win in Shkoder lifts the pressure off manager Alex McLeish after last month's defeat in Israel.Nine call-offs pre-match had left him struggling for options, but his young, energetic side impressed and could have won by more.Reaction and how it happenedMore to follow.Line-upsMatch StatsLive TextLine-upsAlbania1Berisha5Veseli6DjimsitiSubstituted forDermakuat 52'minutes15MavrajBooked at 21mins17Binaku22Uzuni20KaceSubstituted forIsmajliat 27'minutes14Xhaka7GrezdaBooked at 88mins9Memushaj10ManajBooked at 12minsSubstituted forBalajat 62'minutesSubstitutes2Lila3Kaja4Ismajli8Ademi11Vrioni12Kastrati13Lilaj16Ndoj18Dermaku19Balaj21Gavazaj23StrakoshaScotland1McGregor2PatersonBooked at 10mins4BatesBooked at 65mins5McKennaBooked at 60mins3Robertson6McGregor7Forrest8ArmstrongSubstituted forMcTominayat 61'minutes10Christie11FraserSubstituted forRussellat 73'minutesBooked at 80mins9FletcherSubstituted forPhillipsat 68'minutesSubstitutes12Bain14Hendry15Shinnie16Mackay-Steven17McTominay18Phillips19McBurnie20Russell21MacDonaldReferee:Vladislav BezborodovMatch StatsHome TeamAlbaniaAway TeamScotlandPossessionHome58%Away42%ShotsHome7Away20Shots on TargetHome0Away6CornersHome3Away6FoulsHome10Away20Live TextPosted at   Match ends, Albania 0, Scotland 4.Full TimePosted at 90'+4' Second Half ends, Albania 0, Scotland 4.Posted at 90'+1' Ardian Ismajli (Albania) wins a free kick in the attacking half.Posted at 90'+1' Foul by Johnny Russell (Scotland).Posted at 90' Bekim Balaj (Albania) wins a free kick in the attacking half.Posted at 90' Foul by David Bates (Scotland).BookingPosted at 88' Eros Grezda (Albania) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.Posted at 88' Foul by Eros Grezda (Albania).Posted at 88' Scott McTominay (Scot